  "market_context": "Friday, final trading day; bearish external and internal structure on M15; weak Asia session high with equal highs; New York session underway; price had failed to break prior swing low, confirming weakness at the high.",
  "key_observation": "A liquidity sweep occurred at the Asia session high (with equal highs), followed by aggressive break of a bullish FVG on the 5min chart, confirming bearish continuation toward the swing low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified bearish directional bias externally and internally on the 15-minute chart, with a weak high that failed to break the prior swing low.",
    "Step 2: Recognized the Asia session high as a confluence of liquidity: weak high, equal highs, and session-based liquidity concentration.",
    "Step 3: Observed price wick above the high and close back inside — confirming a liquidity sweep of buy-side stops.",
    "Step 4: Switched to 5-minute timeframe and identified a bullish FVG near 1.0875–1.0890 that was holding price; waited for break below it as confirmation.",
    "Step 5: Entered short after price closed below the FVG (inverting it), placing stop loss at the Asia session high (not the immediate sweep high) due to confidence in sweep validity.",
    "Step 6: Set primary target at the swing low (liquidity zone with equal lows and trendline), with secondary target at older 4H low confirmed via higher timeframe analysis.",
    "Step 7: Monitored price reaction post-entry: initial support retest formed new sell-side liquidity, then aggressive break of that level triggered a liquidity run to the downside."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed short after FVG break on 5min; price ran aggressively lower through swing low and continued to secondary target; liquidity run confirmed by strong momentum candles post-break.",
  "lessons": "A liquidity sweep alone is insufficient—requires directional bias, confluence (e.g., Asia high + equal highs), and structural confirmation (e.g., FVG break). Stop placement can be optimized using prior swing highs when sweep is undeniable, improving risk-reward.",
